ented to prevent future accidental commits of secrets. The fact that the credentials were already committed means the password `super_secret_password_123` exists in git history regardless, but at minimum the `.gitignore` should prevent recurrence.\n\nNote: The structural test at `/workspace/tests/structural.test.ts` (lines 78-98) only checks whether `.env` files currently exist with secret content -- it does not validate that `.gitignore` properly excludes `.env`. So this gap is not caught by the test suite.\n\n---\n\n### Verification Results\n\n| Check | Result |\n|-------|--------|\n| `npm run build` | Passes (exit 0) |\n| `npm run lint` | Passes (exit 0) |\n| `npm test` | 49/49 tests pass across 9 test files |\n| Circular dependencies (madge) | None detected |\n| Merge conflict markers | None found |\n| `.env` with secrets | None found |\n\n---\n\n### Issues Summary\n\n**Critical (must fix):** None.\n\n**Important (should fix):**\n1. `/workspace/.gitignore` line 6 -- `.env` is commented out (`# .env`). It should be uncommented to `.env` so that secrets files are properly ignored going forward. Without this fix, the same class of problem (accidentally committed credentials) can recur.\n\n**Suggestions (nice to have):**\n1. `/workspace/packages/core/src/index.ts` -- The `userExists` function is defined in `user.ts` but not re-exported from the barrel file. If it is part of the public API, add it to the exports. If it is intentionally internal, consider adding a comment or prefixing with underscore to signal that intent."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af75330 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 35850\ntool_uses: 40\nduration_ms: 104352</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"78c9c92d-ae6e-4595-853d-fb1fbaf9c15b","uuid":"292cb7ff-56ce-431b-839c-5499c596e839","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Review the implementation changes made to fix the monorepo disaster. The changes fixed 6 issues:\n\n1. C